The paper discusses distributed algorithms for information dissemination in networks, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The specific focus on communication and energy constraints suggests a potential fit for Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The mention of coding-based information dissemination suggests a potential fit for Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the analysis of isoperimetric properties of graphs suggests a potential fit for Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
